The State has made a separate commitment to testing and further dispersion modeling of emissions from the Columbia
Falls Aluminum Company (CFAC) facility. This facility is located outside the nonattainment area and emissions from
CFAC were not identified on the Chemical Mass Balance analysis of filters collected from the monitor in the Columbia
Falls nonattainment area. Emissions from CFAC are a potential concern, however, since this source accounts for 20
percent of the emission inventory (at permitted allowable emissions). EPA will continue to monitor the testing and
assist the State with any action required by the results. 
Section 110(k) of the Act sets out provisions governing EPA's review of SIP submittals (see 57 FR 13565-13566).
In today's action, EPA is proposing to grant approval of those elements of the Columbia Falls PM-10 plan that
were due on November 15, 1991, and submitted by the State on November 25, 1991, and May 6, 1992 (excluding the Kalispell
